                ConferenceRoomId: "e2ff4cbf-1ed8-494b-b6a0-67f19d503769",
                Description:
                    "Time to wash the (sea's?) salty water off your face? Come and disembark at the\r\nFursuit Lounge and freshen up a bit!\r\n\r\nLike every year, we've set up a safe haven for fursuiters (and their stewards)\r\nto stretch their sea legs, where they can cool down, drink something other\r\nthan grog, and have a quick chat with the people they might not have seen in a\r\nwhile… probably because they were out on raids along the coast again. Haven't\r\nbeen there before, or want to know what's changed? Let us talk you\r\nthrough what you can expect!\r\n\r\n### Locations ###\r\n\r\nSince some of our regulars were a bit too rowdy and lit half the nearby town\r\non fire in a drunken stupor a while ago, we've sadly had to relocate slightly\r\nfurther down the coast. While you will still find the small treasure stash,\r\nthe mini lounge, at the same location in the lobby (more on this later), you\r\nwill now find our main lounge further north in the **ECC ROOM (2 &) 3**!\r\n\r\nFrom the Estrel hotel lobby, go north past the mini lounge, **past the\r\ncheckerboard pattern** (\"The Rotunda\"), and **go down**. We suggest taking the\r\nstaircase on port side (left). Then go straight through the (mostly glass) wall and\r\n**keep going straight until you reach the far wall** and, with it, your\r\ndestination! Please ignore any sirens that might try to lure you off course.\r\n\r\nAs always, in case you have any trouble finding your destination, simply\r\nfollow your nose…\r\n\r\n### Services ###\r\n\r\nWhile the past few years of being in hiding (not to mention the relocation… or\r\nthe reparations for that raided village…) have forced us to take a step back,\r\nwe will still do our usual best to tend to your every wish! Below you can find\r\na short summary of what you can expect:\r\n\r\n#### Blowers And Dryers ####\r\n\r\nBreezes aplenty! Please take a seat or a stand in front of our blowers to cool\r\noff. If it's crowded, please keep some distance and share the\r\nbreeze. Likewise, please don't jump in front of people already using them from\r\nslightly further away. For outfits, please (only) use the dryers instead! The\r\nlong tables of pipes are for drying heads (short stubs) and handpaws (longer\r\nsticks), while the airborne pipes in wooden construction are for drying\r\nbodysuits. Try not to keep your stuff on there too long, as space is limited\r\nand demand is high. Otherwise we might need to move your things for you!\r\n\r\n#### Drinks And Snacks ####\r\n\r\nFeel free to try several of our brews! (Sorry, but local laws prohibit\r\nalcohol, so no rum.) Please just make sure you deposit your cup in one of the trashcans\r\nafter, ok? We also try to provide some sugary and salty snacks, so you can leave\r\nwith more energy than you entered with!\r\n\r\n#### Helpers ####\r\n\r\nOur trusty staff is always happy to help you out! Whether it's getting in or\r\nout of suit, grabbing a drink (we know it can be tricky with claws or hooves),\r\nor answering questions, please feel free to ask us and we'll do our best to\r\nget you what you need!\r\n\r\n### Rules ###\r\n\r\nTo avoid getting in trouble with the locals (again…), we're afraid we need to\r\nbe a bit strict about a few things. Always a few privateers ruining it for\r\neveryone else, am I right? Here goes:\r\n\r\n- **Fursuiters Only**\r\n\r\n  You are allowed to take 1 assistant with you, but please make sure that our\r\n  bouncers can see you are together. If you want to get into the lounge while\r\n  not in suit, you will be asked to show your **fursuit badge** (not your\r\n  con badge!) to enter. **Please don't forget to bring it, and do not leave it\r\n  inside!**\r\n\r\n- **No Glass Is Allowed In The Fursuit Lounge**\r\n\r\n  People come here to stretch their legs, not to cut them open on shards!\r\n  Please drink your rum elsewhere. Eye glasses, monocles and spyglasses are\r\n  obviously excluded.\r\n\r\n- **No Blocking Of The Backs Of Fans**\r\n\r\n  We know this is a popular and effective way of drying your gloves and head\r\n  cloths, but please consider that all sweat that is being extracted this way\r\n  is now being blown straight into the faces of anyone sitting on the other\r\n  side.\r\n\r\n- **No Photo Or Video Recording**\r\n\r\n  People come here to relax, not to be wary of anyone taking record of their\r\n  salt-crusted faces. If you want to take pictures, go elsewhere. No\r\n  exceptions.\r\n\r\nPlease don't argue with our staff if they ask you to follow these simple\r\nrules. If you ignore any of these rules, we might be required to move your\r\nthings for you, and we will not be responsible for you finding them again.\r\n\r\n### Mini Lounge ###\r\n\r\nAs always, there is a small lounge with some basic services (mostly blowers\r\nand water), in case you're afraid you won't reach the big fursuit lounge\r\nbefore you run aground. You can find it between the Rotunda and the hotel\r\nlobby. We may not always be there to assist you, but you're free to use what\r\nis available to you there. The same rules apply, though!",
