                ConferenceRoomId: "7fe3490e-bab8-4651-bea5-83d5b545919c",
                Description:
                    "Your personal fursuit badge is not only a nice souvenir for your character; it is also your\r\naccess key to enter the Fursuit Lounge when not wearing a fursuit. While you are in suit, you can always\r\nenter the lounge. You do not need more than one badge, even if you have several suits.\r\n\r\nPlease make sure you already checked in at the Eurofurence Registration Desk before visiting the Fursuit Badge Desk during our service hours.\r\nOn Tuesday and Wednesday, our desk can be found just outside the room with the Registration Desk, in the entrance area to the Rotunda.\r\nFor the rest of the con, we'll be in Estrel Hall B, right next to Registration.\r\n\r\nSince there have been cases in the past of people trying to get fursuit badges just to gain access to the fursuit lounge, we will have to ask you to bring the head of your fursuits along when you come to pick up your fursuit badges so we can compare them to the pictures on the badge.\r\n\r\nIf you pre-registered a fursuit badge, your first badge is free and you can use the fast lane for pickup. If you forgot to pre-register your badge in time, we can also produce your personal fursuit badge on site. For this service and all extra badges, we need to charge you a small fee of 2 Euro per badge.\r\n\r\n### Service hours for pickup and printing\r\n\r\n#### Entrance Rotunda\r\n\r\n**Tuesday:** from when the Eurofurence Registration Desk opens – 19:00. Pickup only!\r\n**Wednesday:** 12:00 – 18:00\r\n\r\n#### Estrel Hall B\r\n\r\n**Thursday:** 11:00 – 13:00 and 16:00 – 18:00\r\n**Friday:** 11:00 – 14:00\r\n\r\nOutside our own service hours you will also be able to pick up pre-ordered badges at the\r\nSecurity Office (as their opening hours allow).",
