                ConferenceTrackId: "0b80cc7b-b5b2-4fab-8b74-078f2b5e366e",
                ConferenceRoomId: "62060c43-76a8-49de-8389-511790f52917",
                Description:
                    "The latest fully illustrated talk from Jonathan Vair Duncan and Sasha R.\r\nJones. We will review the strengths of the furry fandom and what makes it unique from\r\nother fandoms and online communities, and then talk about the ways in which it is and is\r\nnot currently prepared to meet the needs of furries going forward in our changing world.\r\nHow can we use our current strengths to better meet peoples' needs, and to create\r\nresiliency so that we may enjoy the fandom for decades to come? We will balance humor and\r\nearnest sincerity to make these conversations easier for people to engage with, and to\r\nempower them to feel capable of navigating the future. We will introduce topics such as\r\nmutual aid and in-person community building and open the discussion to how these support\r\nnetworks could interface with the furry fandom as an international community.\r\n",
