                ConferenceRoomId: "61c6d51a-a0f4-46ba-a719-d09d859afa26",
                Description:
                    "This year's Art & Charity Auction once again features a multitude of international artists and charity items. Bid on whatever you like and buy art for your home!\r\n\r\nA separate registration is needed to obtain the bid stickers necessary for bidding. \r\n\r\nYou will get a final chance at bidding during the Art Show Closing. Here it will be determined who will make the final offer on a piece of art – or whether, perhaps, a contested piece goes to auction. \r\n\r\nImportant: the closing is a fast and decisive event. You will need to have bid stickers at hand to participate, so we can avoid crowding the show area with spectators. Bid stickers will only be available until 30 minutes before the closing. During the closing, we will not hand out new stickers, so make sure you have enough to place your final bids.\r\n\r\nIn the Art & Charity Auction, you will have to defend your selection of contested pieces against other prospective buyers. Please note that this year's auction starts earlier than in previous years.\r\n\r\nBids must be placed in Euro and paid in cash on site.\r\n\r\nLook out for more information at the Art Show and read the bulletin boards for last-minute details!",
