                Merchandise: "prints, posters, postcards, small books, sketch commissions",
                ShortDescription:
                    "I'm a color-loving German illustrator of real and imaginary creatures and an advocate of all animals. I’m the creator of the recently launched webcomic Being Monsters. I'll bring prints and books to EF, and I'll also be taking a very limited number of commissions.",
                AboutTheArtistText:
                    "I'm a German freelance illustrator and usually run under my full name Julia Beutling. Iove colour, I depict real and imaginary creatures, and I’m an advocate of all animals. Since I launched my webcomic Being Monsters at the end of 2021, I can now officially call myself a comic creator, as well. I also made a number of personal illustrated books and poster series throughout the years.",
                AboutTheArtText:
                    "Art: \r\nMy illustrations show my partiality for nature and real animals, but I really enjoy taking trips into the realm of fairy tales and myths to return with a horde of mermaids, unicorns or talking monsters.\r\n\r\nComic: \r\nMy ongoing, long-format webcomic Being Monsters is a modern, very free adaption of the classic fairy tale of Beauty and the Beast, in which a spiky young activist has to deal with an actual terrifying Monster, a conservative little village and her messed-up live in parallel. It’s much more a drama and a detective story than a romance.\r\nYou can read it for free on www.beingmonsters.com or on Webtoon.\r\n\r\nAt EF: \r\nI’ll bring my illustration series and books to the Dealer’s Den again (Junicorn, Tiny Inklings, Morph, etc.), and I'll have a few originals in the art show. I’ll also be taking a very limited number of my rare commissions at EF, so be quick if you want one!",
